Perfect Strike			KEY:Kensai ~ Perfect Strike				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:MagusClassFeatures.Extraordinary.ArchetypeAbility.SpecialQuality																DESC:At 4th level, when a kensai hits with his chosen weapon, he can spend 1 point from his arcane pool in order to maximize his weapon damage. Don't roll for damage-the weapon deals maximum damage. This affects only the weapon's base damage dice, not additional damage from sneak attack, magical weapon properties, spellstrike, or critical hits. If the kensai confirms a critical hit, he can instead spend 2 points from his arcane pool to increase his weapon's critical multiplier by 1. This ability replaces spell recall.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Fighter Training			KEY:Kensai ~ Fighter Training				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:MagusClassFeatures.Extraordinary.ArchetypeAbility.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:FighterLevelQualify|0					DESC:Starting at 7th level, a kensai counts his magus level -3 as his fighter level for the purpose of qualifying for feats (if he has levels in fighter, these levels stack), but forfeits the benefit of such feats with weapons other than his favored weapon. This ability replaces knowledge pool.																																																																																																																																							ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|TYPE=FighterWeaponQualify																																																																																BONUS:VAR|FighterLevelQualify|FighterWeaponQualifyLVL																														BONUS:VAR|FighterWeaponQualifyLVL|MagusLVL-3|TYPE=Base																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Iaijutsu				KEY:Kensai ~ Iaijutsu					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:MagusClassFeatures.Extraordinary.ArchetypeAbility.SpecialQuality																DESC:At 7th level, a kensai applies his Intelligence modifier as well as his Dexterity modifier on initiative rolls (minimum 0). A kensai may make attacks of opportunity when flat-footed, and may draw his favored weapon as a free action as part of taking an attack of opportunity. This ability replaces the medium armor ability.																																																																																																																																																																																																																													BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|max(INT,0)																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Critical Perfection		KEY:Kensai ~ Critical Perfection			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:MagusClassFeatures.Extraordinary.ArchetypeAbility.SpecialQuality			DEFINE:CriticalFocusQualify|0									DESC:At 9th level, a kensai adds his Intelligence bonus (minimum 0) on critical hit confirmation rolls with his favored weapon. In addition, the kensai may use his magus levels in place of his base attack bonuses to qualify for Critical Focus and any feat for which it is a prerequisite; these feats apply only with a kensai's favored weapon. This ability replaces the magus arcana normally gained at 9th level.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											BONUS:VAR|CriticalFocusQualify|classlevel("Magus")																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Superior Reflexes			KEY:Kensai ~ Superior Reflexes			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:MagusClassFeatures.Extraordinary.ArchetypeAbility.SpecialQuality																DESC:At 11th level, kensai can make a number of attacks of opportunity in a round equal to his Intelligence modifier (minimum 1). This effect stacks with the Combat Reflexes feat. This ability replaces improved spell recall.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Iaijutsu Focus			KEY:Kensai ~ Iaijutsu Focus				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:MagusClassFeatures.Extraordinary.ArchetypeAbility.SpecialQuality																DESC:At 13th level, a kensai may always act and may draw his weapon as a swift action during a surprise round, though he is considered flat-footed until he acts. During a surprise round or when attacking a flat-footed opponent, he adds his Intelligence modifier on damage with his chosen weapon (minimum 0). This ability replaces heavy armor.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Iaijutsu Master			KEY:Kensai ~ Iaijutsu Master				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:MagusClassFeatures.Extraordinary.ArchetypeAbility.SpecialQuality																DESC:At 19th level, a kensai's initiative roll is automatically a natural 20 and he is never surprised. This ability replaces greater spell access.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Weapon Mastery			KEY:Kensai ~ Weapon Mastery				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:MagusClassFeatures.Extraordinary.ArchetypeAbility.SpecialQuality																DESC:At 20th level, a kensai gains weapon mastery with his favored weapon, as the fighter class ability. This ability replaces true magus.																																																																																																																																																																																																																		BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Weapon Mastery|1																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.55
